1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,736
(Previously)
Have you figured it out now?

2
00:00:01,760 --> 00:00:03,120
About our status.

3
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:07,440
To be honest, I still
can't give you an answer.

4
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,440
Rome!
You don't get to interfere.

5
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:14,680
Don't forget, we're nothing to each other.

6
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:17,720
Besides, doesn't Tua like Arnold?

7
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,640
How do you think he feels
watching you do that?

8
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:20,800
I talked to him.

9
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,400
He gave me the green light.

10
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:23,600
What did I tell you, Jack?

11
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:24,920
I'd get those followers for you.

12
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:26,000
So, this is me.

13
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:27,280
The new Dean.

14
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,440
(Episode 6: Building a Relationship)

15
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:35,280
Awww! #ArnoldDean
Love thisss #ArnoldDean

16
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:36,520
I'm screaming, they're perfect #ArnoldDean
Great chemistry #ArnoldDean

17
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:38,120
So cuteeee #ArnoldDean

18
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:42,359
Can't stop smiling #ArnoldDean

19
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:43,679
They're boyfies, don't tell me otherwise
#ArnoldDean

20
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:44,960
I get butterflies #ArnoldDean

21
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:47,960
Give me more #ArnoldDean

22
00:00:47,961 --> 00:00:48,999
It's not a ship, it's real #ArnoldDean

23
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,039
Keep it coming pls #ArnoldDean

24
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:51,159
I smile so much my lips hurt #ArnoldDean

25
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:52,560
Argh!! Biting my pillow #ArnoldDean

26
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,079
They're lucky #ArnoldDean

27
00:00:58,080 --> 00:00:59,559
Ship of the year #ArnoldDean

28
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:00,959
Loveee #ArnoldDean

29
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:02,360
Give us a fan meeting #ArnoldDean

30
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:11,840
Loving thisss #ArnoldDean
The captain himself is sailing #ArnoldDean

31
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:13,400
Arnold the microwave, only warm for Dean
#ArnoldDean

32
00:01:13,401 --> 00:01:15,961
0.5 seconds eye contact equals
million unspoken words #ArnoldDean

33
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
"Only Friends : Dream On"

34
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,680
Aren't you afraid,
coming to see me like this?

35
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:15,520
If we're in love, what
is there to be afraid of?

36
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,320
Cut!

37
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,360
It's already a kiss scene,
but I'm still not feeling anything.

38
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,120
You're not?

39
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,720
I felt plenty just now.

40
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:48,880
Mhm. We felt it more than last rehearsal.

41
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,800
But it's not reaching the audience.

42
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:55,080
If the chemistry's
real, I should feel it too.

43
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:59,080
Is our chemistry off,
or are you just in a bad mood?

44
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,440
As the director,

45
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:14,160
tell us how to kiss so
the audience feels it.

46
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:17,640
Well?

47
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,240
How is it?

48
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:21,320
How should we kiss?

49
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,200
Like that.

50
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Why don't you get it?

51
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,400
That's just how our director is.

52
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,920
Hard to get. All over the place.

53
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,040
Let's just call it a day.

54
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,000
Alright, everyone, that's a wrap.

55
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:14,400
You're free to go.

56
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:15,720
Nothing.

57
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,480
Their chemistry just wasn't there.

58
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,480
What's with you? Why so moody?

59
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,440
I'm fine.

60
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,760
This is "fine"? Hm?

61
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:46,800
Or are you unhappy about Arnold and me?

62
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,080
Why would I be?

63
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,560
Everything's normal.

64
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:56,200
If you're not okay with it,
you can tell everyone we're back together.

65
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,640
We're just on good terms now.

66
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,120
We're not back together.

67
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:06,600
Besides, what you're doing
is good for the play.

68
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,520
You've created buzz. Tickets are selling.

69
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:10,920
So, thanks for that.

70
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,160
What do you want exactly?

71
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:15,240
You say no to this, no to that.

72
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:18,400
Are you just going to
stay jealous of Arnold and me like this?

73
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,880
Fine.

74
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,280
I'll get used to it eventually.

75
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,280
Earlier, it just caught me off guard.

76
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,400
Okay.

77
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,240
Hey.

78
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,320
Arnold and I, it's just for content.

79
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,440
Got it?

80
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,360
Hey.

81
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:55,880
What are you doing?

82
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,320
People can see.

83
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,520
Now you're shy?

84
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,920
You just kissed me
in front of everyone in the room.

85
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:05,160
No one keeps up with Jack like I do.

86
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,520
Why isn't he picking up?

87
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,480
Hello.
Where are you?

88
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,720
(Not your concern.)

89
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:31,960
(I'm busy.)

90
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:32,760
(I'm hanging up.)

91
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,040
Hey, wait.

92
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,600
What's his problem?

93
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:16,640
I'll get back at you. Someone's calling.

94
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:20,760
Hello, Dean?

95
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,440
Yeah, sure.

96
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:25,000
Send me the details.

97
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:27,840
Okay.

98
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,440
What did Dean say?

99
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:34,120
We've got work tomorrow.

100
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:36,480
We need to film some sponsored content.

101
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:38,960
Mm.

102
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,480
Hey, what's up with Jack and Dean?

103
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:44,200
I heard they broke up.

104
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,520
But at rehearsal… oh, wow.

105
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,840
It looked like Jack was jealous.

106
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,640
It wasn't just that he looked like it.

107
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,240
I think he was really jealous.

108
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:55,440
Right? That's what I thought too.

109
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,640
I was shocked when
Jack pulled Dean in and kissed him.

110
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,360
I was shocked as well.

111
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,400
Exactly.

112
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:03,760
Is the director going to have me killed?

113
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:06,120
I still have to film
fan-service content with Dean.

114
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,040
Come on. No.

115
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,680
That's just how friends are.

116
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,376
You can't fully cut each other off.

117
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,840
That's why things stay unresolved.

118
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,200
I knew it.

119
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,640
Knew what?

120
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:22,400
Going from friends to lovers.

121
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,000
It'll never work out.

122
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,560
In the end, you break up.

123
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,480
You lose the relationship,
and the friendship goes with it.

124
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,120
Hey, that can't be true for everyone.

125
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,560
Some couples make it work.

126
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:46,400
Right?

127
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:47,880
Are you okay?

128
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,280
I am.

129
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:52,120
I'm thinking the same thing you are.

130
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,120
I said something that set him off again.

131
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,840
Guess I can never change his viewpoint.

132
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:06,280
I just have to accept it.

133
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,840
You're playing really good music today.

134
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:34,240
Thank you.

135
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:38,400
Actually, it's not just your music I like.

136
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:42,120
I'm glad you asked me out.

137
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,240
I'm glad you came.

138
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,120
So after this,

139
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,680
can I come over to your place
and listen to more music?

140
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,480
Rome.

141
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,080
Excuse me.

142
00:11:11,326 --> 00:11:12,726
I need to discuss something urgent.

143
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,400
Be right back.

144
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,440
What is it?

145
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,000
I told you, I'm busy.

146
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,360
Come with me after work.

147
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,680
We're not together.

148
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,760
You don't get to drag me around.

149
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,440
You do realize that, right?

150
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,760
Are you jealous of Boston and me?

151
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,560
No.

152
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:40,600
Whether you want to go with
Boston or Jack, that's your choice.

153
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,720
Will you stop being sarcastic?

154
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,520
That's my choice.

155
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,200
I think I'll go back to my fun life.

156
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:52,880
This is what you want?

157
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,320
Mm.

158
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,080
I'm busy.

159
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,840
When I'm free and
there's no one else around,

160
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,080
I'll come back and play with you.

161
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,080
Let's go.

162
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:16,360
Someone like him
should see this side of me.

163
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,800
Actually, ignoring him is just an act.

164
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,280
It doesn't get me anything.

165
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,320
Timmy.

166
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,520
Where are Dean and Arnold?

167
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:41,640
They'll be here.

168
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,520
Have someone stand in for them for now.

169
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:48,320
A stand-in won't feel the same
as the actual actors. Right?

170
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,360
They're running half an hour late.

171
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:54,359
They're filming sponsored content.

172
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,360
They'll be here soon.

173
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,600
I've been waiting for an hour.

174
00:12:58,040 --> 00:13:00,320
Is the whole production
supposed to wait for them?

175
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,040
I don't think it's acceptable.

176
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,600
Should I rehearse with a stagehand first?

177
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,520
No.

178
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:13,000
I'll call them right now.

179
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,040
Don't.

180
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:16,520
I'll go find them myself.

181
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,640
He double-cast me,

182
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:29,360
and I haven't even
had a proper rehearsal yet.

183
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:01,600
Cut.

184
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:02,920
Pass.

185
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,200
Change the angle.

186
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,400
Dean, Arnold, come take a look.

187
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:08,960
Thank you.

188
00:14:08,961 --> 00:14:10,000
Wut, play that back.

189
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:12,280
How was it?

190
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,240
You both did great. I like it.

191
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:18,200
Especially you, Dean. You see?
Your emotions and your eyes.

192
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:22,640
Oh, I have a new series coming up.

193
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,360
Would you be interested in auditioning?

194
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:26,960
Of course.

195
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,120
I'd love to.

196
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,960
Good. I'll have my team contact you.

197
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,480
Thank you.

198
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:37,360
Hey, are you the next superstar or what?

199
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:40,080
I'm happy for you.

200
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:44,320
Hey, I really have to thank you
for filming content with me.

201
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:49,079
Damn. I never thought being shipped
with you would get me this far.

202
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:51,960
No problem, Dean. I'm getting paid too.

203
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:54,280
And I really enjoy working with you.

204
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,400
What are you two doing?

205
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,240
Why are you here?

206
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:05,280
No. Why are you still here?

207
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:06,800
Why aren't you at rehearsal?

208
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:10,000
I sent you a message. I said we'd be late.

209
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:13,080
You said half an hour. It's been two hours.

210
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:16,200
Jack, please calm down.

211
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,599
Dean, Arnold, if you're ready, head to set.

212
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,200
Everything's ready.

213
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,320
I'm sorry, sir.

214
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,080
We have to get back to rehearsal now.

215
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Jack.

216
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:31,480
I understand my actors
need to film sponsored content.

217
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:34,680
But if it takes this
long, my play will fail.

218
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:40,400
Boy, if you don't have sponsors,
your play will fail anyway.

219
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,440
Hey, Jack.

220
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,480
That's enough.

221
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:46,080
I want to finish filming.

222
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,400
Please.

223
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,520
I'm sorry, sir.

224
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:02,960
Let's continue.

225
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,000
You're ready to film now?

226
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:04,880
Yes.

227
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,160
Alright, let's resume.

228
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:07,640
Hey, let's shoot.

229
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,600
Go get ready, you two.

230
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,559
Cheers!

231
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:19,960
Drink up, drink up.

232
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,400
Raffy, what's wrong?

233
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,120
You're not feeling it.

234
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,960
It's my birthday. Have fun.

235
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,160
Come on, man.

236
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,880
For the birthday boy.

237
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:36,560
That's right. And it's his treat.

238
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,120
No idea where he got the money.

239
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:41,120
We usually split the bill on his birthday.

240
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,680
I don't do this often.

241
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,240
This is a special occasion.

242
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:45,880
Order what you want.
Special, it is.

243
00:16:46,521 --> 00:16:47,600
Go on.

244
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,800
You keep staring.

245
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,160
Do you like him?

246
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,160
Hey!

247
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,080
No. I'm just looking.

248
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:07,080
Just looking, huh?

249
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:09,280
Raffy, are you tight with Rome?

250
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:14,800
No.

251
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:15,920
We work in different areas.

252
00:17:16,360 --> 00:17:17,360
Why do you ask?

253
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:18,520
Nothing.

254
00:17:18,713 --> 00:17:20,193
I just see Pete staring.

255
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,520
Why don't you help him out?

256
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,240
Hey, no.

257
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:25,360
Are you crazy?

258
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,479
Come on, that's your birthday gift.

259
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:28,160
Don't you want it?
Say yes, my friend.

260
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,080
No way.

261
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:32,880
Be bold. Go on.

262
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:36,880
If Raffy won't help, go tell him yourself.

263
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:40,880
"Please be my birthday present."

264
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:41,640
Go on.

265
00:17:41,641 --> 00:17:42,840
Get up.

266
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:43,800
Get your ass up.

267
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:45,455
Stand up. Stand up.

268
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,040
Just go.
Do it.

269
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:47,680
Are you guys serious?
Hurry up.

270
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,360
Go on.

271
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:50,720
- Really?
- Come on. Go already.

272
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:53,160
Chop-chop.

273
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,160
Here he comes.

274
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:19,080
Rome, have a seat.

275
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,240
Please.

276
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,319
Guys, say hi to Rome.

277
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:24,680
Cheers.

278
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,080
Cheers.

279
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:34,280
Hey. How's it going as a sound
engineer for the faculty play?

280
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:35,640
Having fun?

281
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,440
It's pretty fun.

282
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,616
I get to meet people from other majors too.

283
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,520
Usually, I only hang out with music people.

284
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:45,640
It's a shame I'm an accountant.

285
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:47,840
I don't get to see you much.

286
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:51,120
But I think Raffy sees you a lot.

287
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:54,080
I told you I don't. I'm not close to him.

288
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:55,520
We work in different areas.

289
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:57,880
We do see each other.

290
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:01,760
At the play and outside of it too.

291
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,520
I don't really pay attention.

292
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,840
Yeah? I think you do.

293
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,640
Pete.

294
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:17,040
Hm?

295
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,200
Happy birthday.

296
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:20,040
Hope you get what you want.

297
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:23,480
Lucky in game and lucky in love.

298
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,200
Thank you, Rome.

299
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:38,160
Would you excuse me?

300
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,200
I'm going to grab something from my car.

301
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,200
Rome.

302
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:49,840
Uh… I'll go with you.

303
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:52,040
Mm.

304
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,000
Nice!
Awesome.

305
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:03,840
Cheers.

306
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,640
Hey.

307
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,000
Why are you here so early?

308
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:25,200
I knew you'd be busy,
so I asked to leave early.

309
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:28,520
I also knew you'd be working so hard
you wouldn't eat,

310
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:31,800
so I got you the famous Pad Thai
near Pink's.

311
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:33,880
Thanks.

312
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,400
Don't thank me.

313
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,479
Stop working and eat first.

314
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:38,480
You need the energy.

315
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:40,120
I'm helping you tonight.

316
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:55,720
Tua.

317
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,840
I'm sorry. I've been really busy lately.

318
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:04,320
Between classes, rehearsals,
filming with Dean,

319
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,080
and my part-time job at Pink's,

320
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,480
I barely have time for you.

321
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:13,240
If you're that tired, you don't have to
go out of your way to see me.

322
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:18,160
Seeing you doesn't make me more tired.

323
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:20,280
It makes me happier.

324
00:21:24,160 --> 00:21:26,160
If you're happy, then I'm okay.

325
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:39,720
Hey.

326
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,880
I told them not to add bean sprouts.

327
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,200
Here, let me eat them for you.

328
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:49,720
Give me the bean sprouts,
and you take the shrimp.

329
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:51,560
Here.

330
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:54,599
You haven't peeled it.
How am I supposed to eat it?

331
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,080
You're right.

332
00:21:55,560 --> 00:21:56,560
Okay.

333
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,440
Here you go, sir.

334
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,880
Good?

335
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:23,360
It's good.

336
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:27,960
Special bite.

337
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:28,840
Special?

338
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:29,920
It's so good.

339
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,080
How come yours tastes better than mine?

340
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:39,320
Because I fed you.

341
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,040
Hey.

342
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,320
Rome, why don't you get in the car?

343
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,080
What is it, Pete?

344
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:33,600
I like you, Rome.

345
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:36,880
Thank you.

346
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:39,640
If…

347
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,720
If we do it in the car, would you mind?

348
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,640
Don't you want to think it through first?

349
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:21,040
I got you some premium matcha.

350
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,480
You can drink it when you're stressed.

351
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:28,640
You had time to go shopping?

352
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:30,960
I thought you only had time for content.

353
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:34,680
Come on.

354
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:37,880
Are you still mad at me?

355
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,000
I have every right to be.

356
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:42,640
You kept people waiting.

357
00:24:48,280 --> 00:24:49,280
Alright.

358
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,040
I'm sorry.

359
00:24:57,080 --> 00:25:00,480
But you shouldn't have done that on set.

360
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:09,400
You know that was my opportunity.

361
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:12,720
Is this really what you want?

362
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:15,720
All you do is create hype around your ship.

363
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,120
Are you actually happy with that?

364
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,120
Jack.

365
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:24,480
You know why I have to do this.

366
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:27,160
Honestly, I don't like it either.

367
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:29,240
But who would've thought

368
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:36,040
this would get me closer to my dream
of becoming an actor?

369
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:43,320
I promise it won't
affect your play again.

370
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:49,200
I know how important
this play is to you.

371
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:54,920
And I want to give my best performance,

372
00:25:55,793 --> 00:25:58,313
to live up to being your number one actor.

373
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:03,120
Mm.

374
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,920
Just don't let it happen again.

375
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,640
So…

376
00:26:15,920 --> 00:26:17,480
can I stay over?

377
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:22,520
So you can punish me however you want.

378
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:28,000
It was a serious offense.

379
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:30,520
Mm.

380
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:32,360
If it's that serious,

381
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,160
then I truly deserve to be punished.

382
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:43,600
Hey.

383
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:45,759
You can just sit and cheer me on.

384
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:47,080
You don't have to actually do it.

385
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:50,960
I want to help so you can finish it faster.

386
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:56,120
The way I see it, it
might take even longer.

387
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:58,840
Don't tease me.

388
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,120
Hey.

389
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:06,880
Since becoming your friend,

390
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:08,960
I've gotten to do so many fun things.

391
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:12,640
Shopped for fabric in Little India,

392
00:28:13,280 --> 00:28:16,360
tried Indian food, and
even acted in a play.

393
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:18,039
Stick with me,

394
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:19,960
and you'll get to do even more.

395
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:21,920
Yeah.

396
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:24,560
I spend so much time with you
that my friends tease me.

397
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:27,080
"Arnold, acting major."

398
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:29,320
Ow.

399
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:31,959
Hey, are you okay?

400
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:33,960
I'm fine. Just a little cut.

401
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:36,440
Hold on.

402
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:45,920
Here.

403
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,640
Press on it.

404
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:57,719
I told you I'd do it.

405
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:58,760
You didn't listen.

406
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:10,919
Sit and rest.

407
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:11,920
I'll handle it.

408
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:15,880
Mm, I'll let you do it
so you can finish faster.

409
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,240
I'll just sit here and cheer you on.

410
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,440
What did you even do?

411
00:29:31,480 --> 00:29:33,560
It's the effort that counts.

412
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:39,080
Just being with him like this
makes me happy.

413
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:01,719
Right now, Hype Wave FM is joined by

414
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:03,439
the cast of the play

415
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:06,840
everyone's talking about on social media.

416
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:08,679
They're right here with us.

417
00:30:08,680 --> 00:30:15,199
Please welcome the team
from the play Romeo &amp; Romeo!

418
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:16,839
Hello.

419
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:17,760
Hi.
Hi, welcome.

420
00:30:18,681 --> 00:30:19,959
You guys are so cute.

421
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:21,440
I can confirm that with my own eyes.

422
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:23,960
The whole team is here in this studio.

423
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:28,560
Before we get into the play,
can I be a shipper for a moment?

424
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,919
Because I just have to ship.

425
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:34,279
I'm talking about #ArnoldDean.

426
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:37,400
The buzz around them
is just as big as the play itself.

427
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:39,039
The chemistry is amazing.

428
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:42,440
Why don't we let the two of them
say something to the fans?

429
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:45,199
Let me give you a little spoiler.

430
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:48,000
Our chemistry in the play
is even better than this.

431
00:30:48,336 --> 00:30:50,775
If you want the full experience,
don't forget to grab your tickets.

432
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:53,440
That's right. We'll be waiting for you.

433
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:56,279
Gosh, they'll be waiting for us.

434
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:57,919
I'm smiling without even realizing it.

435
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,200
I don't even know why, but I am.

436
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:02,360
Why?

437
00:31:02,361 --> 00:31:03,720
Because they feel so real.

438
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:05,840
It doesn't feel like just a ship at all.

439
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:06,920
Let's do this.

440
00:31:06,921 --> 00:31:08,239
We'll welcome the comments.

441
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:13,159
If you're watching live and
you ship #ArnoldDean, drop a comment.

442
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:14,919
WANNA HIT PINK'S CLUB TMR?
I'll read it out loud.

443
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:15,480
WANNA HIT PINK'S CLUB TMR?
Let's go.
GOING FOR THE DRINKS OR FOR ROME?
Let's go.

444
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:17,080
GOING FOR THE DRINKS OR FOR ROME?
Here's the first one with #ArnoldDean:

445
00:31:17,841 --> 00:31:20,640
FOR ROME. JUST KIDDING.
Here's the first one with #ArnoldDean:

446
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,279
OOH! THAT NIGHT IN THE CAR
MUST'VE BEEN REAL GOOD.

447
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:23,359
"They feel more real than just a ship."

448
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:24,759
STOP TEASING ME.
"They feel more real than just a ship."

449
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:26,680
STOP TEASING ME.
"I ship them so hard."

450
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:29,040
Here's another one.

451
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:35,440
Next: "I love Arnold so much,
but I love him even more with Dean."

452
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:38,279
Alright. I kind of agree.

453
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,599
Last one: "The MC should see a dentist.
(What's up?)

454
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:42,719
Last one: "The MC should see a dentist.

455
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,679
You can't stop smiling."

456
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:45,999
Okay, I'm sorry, guys.

457
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,360
I'm just getting too excited.

458
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:50,119
Our livestream is blowing up right now.

459
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:53,119
We've never had this many viewers before.

460
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:54,639
Alright, this one's interesting:

461
00:31:54,640 --> 00:32:00,680
"I want to see Dean and Arnold
make a heart together."

462
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,000
Wow.

463
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,160
Go on, you two.
Look at this camera.

464
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:04,920
Okay.

465
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:08,760
And there's the heart.

466
00:32:08,761 --> 00:32:10,320
Everyone, screenshot that right now.

467
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:11,640
Capture it.

468
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:12,680
Excuse me!

469
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:16,720
Should we talk about the play now?

470
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:23,560
Right, let's get into it.

471
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:29,040
Now that you've seen the
chemistry between our leads,

472
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:32,159
don't forget to grab your tickets
and come see us.

473
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:35,039
Everyone's been working so hard,
without pay.

474
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:35,840
Wait, what?

475
00:32:35,841 --> 00:32:37,960
You're doing this for free?

476
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:39,280
That's right.

477
00:32:39,281 --> 00:32:41,479
They're giving it their all.

478
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:47,920
Even if we're not getting paid,
we hope the happiness we share is worth it.

479
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:49,439
That's so sweet.

480
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:51,119
They're really working hard, you guys.

481
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:53,480
They have a passion for stage plays.

482
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:56,880
Holy shit.

483
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,280
Why is everyone else
not getting paid, but I am?

484
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,920
Hey, take it easy. Don't get upset.

485
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:15,640
It's really not a big deal.

486
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:16,720
Not a big deal?

487
00:33:29,320 --> 00:33:30,560
Then explain it.

488
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:33,320
Where did the rehearsal pay come from?

489
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:37,399
Please don't hate me.

490
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:38,480
I meant well.

491
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:42,400
Actually…

492
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:46,960
I'm the one who hired you.

493
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:50,120
Why would you do that, Tua?

494
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:53,320
Do you think I have to work to survive?

495
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:55,480
Why? Do you feel sorry for me?

496
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:57,040
It's not like that.

497
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:58,560
I'm sorry.

498
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:01,840
Please don't worry.

499
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,200
I haven't told anyone.

500
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:09,160
I mean, if you're worried
people might judge you, they won't.

501
00:34:09,473 --> 00:34:13,473
Tua, do you even hear yourself? Huh?

502
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:17,560
What you're doing
feels like you're buying me.

503
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:20,040
Do you think I'm that money-hungry?

504
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:24,520
Hey, I don't want you to feel that way.

505
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,799
I just didn't want you to struggle.

506
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:29,439
Just think of it as a job.

507
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:31,320
Once it's done, you get paid. It's over.

508
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:33,560
Do you really think
I want your money that badly?

509
00:34:34,640 --> 00:34:36,640
I thought you knew me better than that.

510
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:39,200
I trusted you.

511
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,999
I didn't think you'd do this to me.

512
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:42,000
Hey.

513
00:34:53,680 --> 00:34:54,680
What's wrong?

514
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:56,520
You've looked irritated since the studio.

515
00:34:57,680 --> 00:34:58,680
I'm fine.

516
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:00,440
Where are you headed?

517
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:02,000
Want a ride?

518
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,360
No.

519
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:04,840
I don't want to get in your car.

520
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,880
I don't want to take someone else's place.

521
00:35:11,720 --> 00:35:12,880
You mean Pete?

522
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,000
Yeah.

523
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:17,120
Did you bring someone else there too?

524
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:21,320
But it's none of my business who you bring.

525
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:22,840
I don't care.

526
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:26,240
Hey. You don't have to worry
about taking anyone's place.

527
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:28,520
Pete and I didn't do anything that night.

528
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:33,080
It was practically a lamb to the slaughter
and you didn't go for it?

529
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,040
I'd be stupid to believe that.

530
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:37,360
So you don't believe me?

531
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:47,680
You can listen to
the recording from my dash cam.

532
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:49,640
Here.

533
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:02,120
I don't think we should, Pete.

534
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,080
Why not?

535
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:10,320
I don't want to.

536
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:13,800
And I have to DJ later.

537
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:17,120
It'll be quick.

538
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:19,200
I'm sorry, Pete.

539
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:21,760
I don't think this is a good idea.

540
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:23,680
Let's get out of the car.

541
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:37,920
Do you believe me now?

542
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,400
Pete and I didn't do anything.

543
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:43,240
Then why did he say you did?

544
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:45,160
Don't know.

545
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:47,960
Maybe he just wants to brag
he hooked up with someone hot like me.

546
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:49,120
Everyone wants to claim me.

547
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:51,320
It's nice though.

548
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,240
Seeing you jealous.

549
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:55,880
What?

550
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:57,160
Who's jealous?

551
00:36:58,040 --> 00:37:00,960
I just don't like sharing
stuff with my friend.

552
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:04,760
Rest assured now.

553
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:06,880
I'm clean food.

554
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:08,960
Ready for you to eat.

555
00:37:09,120 --> 00:37:11,440
The more you have, the healthier you get.

556
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:14,880
You're not "clean."

557
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:16,920
Who knows what processes
you've been through?

558
00:37:17,200 --> 00:37:18,200
Not healthy.

559
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:19,680
Still tastes good though, right?

560
00:37:20,680 --> 00:37:21,960
You keep coming back for more.

561
00:37:24,520 --> 00:37:25,080
Come on.

562
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,240
I'll give you a ride.

563
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:27,680
Come.

564
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:35,600
Damn you, Jack.

565
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,696
You really don't know
when to compromise, do you?

566
00:37:37,720 --> 00:37:39,440
You killed the vibe the MC built up.

567
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:43,440
I wanted people to focus on the play.

568
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:46,480
Or what?

569
00:37:46,640 --> 00:37:48,080
You want me to make an announcement?

570
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:50,120
"Our ship is just a ship."

571
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:52,440
"My real man is the director."

572
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:54,760
"And he's way spicier than his stage play."

573
00:37:59,640 --> 00:38:00,560
Right here?
Mm.

574
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:11,200
When you act,
do you ever fall for your co-stars?

575
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:13,800
No.

576
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:15,880
I think I'm pretty good.

577
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:19,040
Acting is acting. Reality is reality.

578
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:21,960
Why do you ask?

579
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:26,560
I just wanted to know.

580
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:31,000
Do you think I'm into Arnold?

581
00:38:37,600 --> 00:38:38,880
Well…

582
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,400
Sometimes it feels that way.

583
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:43,519
Then maybe you should compliment me.

584
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:46,560
It means I'm acting well enough
to make you believe it.

585
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:50,440
No. I'm not complimenting you.

586
00:38:52,600 --> 00:38:54,160
You're always like this.

587
00:38:54,680 --> 00:38:58,519
I don't get praise when I do something
right, but I get yelled at when I mess up.

588
00:38:58,520 --> 00:39:00,720
Someone like you deserves to be yelled at.

589
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:08,800
Jack.

590
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:15,040
When I said I wanted to be a better person,

591
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,960
it was because of you.

592
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:23,040
I like it the most when I'm with you.

593
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:26,400
You don't have to do it for me.

594
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:29,440
Do it for yourself.

595
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:37,839
Well, if I become better,
that just means you get a better boyfriend.

596
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:38,480
Right?

597
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:39,680
Hey.

598
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:41,800
We're not back together yet.

599
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:44,136
How many times do I
have to tell you that?

600
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:45,880
Then I'll keep saying
it until you give in.

601
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:52,240
Stop talking and start
filming the casting video.

602
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:54,960
Then we can lie down and watch a movie.

603
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:57,400
Alright.
I'm ready.

604
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:00,640
Move a little to your left.

605
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:02,960
Good?

606
00:40:04,120 --> 00:40:05,360
Okay. Stay like that.

607
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:07,160
Alright.

608
00:40:07,600 --> 00:40:10,000
Five, four, three, two, action.

609
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:34,480
HOW DO YOU GET SOMEONE
TO STOP BEING MAD AT YOU?

610
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:38,319
THERE'S NO SINGLE WAY
THAT WORKS FOR EVERYONE.

611
00:40:38,320 --> 00:40:40,839
BUT SOME THINGS HELP.
1. GIVE THEM TIME.

612
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:46,839
20,000฿ HAS BEEN
TRANSFERRED TO YOUR ACCOUNT.

613
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:51,160
CURRENT BALANCE: 230,050฿

614
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:59,400
Did you really bring me to a concert?

615
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:03,280
In a place like this?

616
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:05,319
I thought we'd be going to a concert hall.

617
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:06,480
This is the place.

618
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:09,640
It's an underground show.

619
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:13,120
It's cool because you only find out
which venue 36 hours before,

620
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:15,959
and you don't even know who's performing.

621
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:16,960
Surprising, right?

622
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:18,800
And how did you even find out about this?

623
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:21,520
My seniors are hosting it.

624
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:25,000
They love going to concerts, so they
started organizing shows themselves.

625
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:26,520
Extreme, huh?

626
00:41:27,640 --> 00:41:29,520
But I think you know them.

627
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:33,320
Here they are.

628
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:34,480
Sand, Ray.

629
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:39,800
What's up?
Have you been well?

630
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:42,000
I have. Thank you.

631
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:44,536
I haven't seen you guys
since the seniors' farewell party.

632
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:46,520
But I've been following
you on social media.

633
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:50,120
We've been busy with shows
and this craft beer.

634
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:52,520
Give it a try.

635
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:55,440
This one's brewed from
all my years of drinking experience.

636
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:56,920
Tell me what you think.

637
00:42:05,200 --> 00:42:06,200
It's good.

638
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:08,056
You're doing all this on your own?

639
00:42:08,080 --> 00:42:09,080
Yeah.

640
00:42:10,760 --> 00:42:11,600
Well, not exactly.

641
00:42:11,601 --> 00:42:12,841
I'm doing it with my boyfriend.

642
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:14,080
Oh, wow.

643
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:15,760
Long time no see,

644
00:42:16,080 --> 00:42:17,400
and you're still such a show-off.

645
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:19,360
So what's this?

646
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:21,640
Introducing your boyfriend at my event?

647
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:24,559
Hey, no.

648
00:42:24,560 --> 00:42:25,879
We're just friends.

649
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:28,600
He likes to party, so I brought him along.

650
00:42:30,440 --> 00:42:33,320
Sounds more like an excuse to flirt.

651
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:41,520
We're really just friends.

652
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:45,400
Okay.

653
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:46,600
Friends, it is.

654
00:42:46,720 --> 00:42:47,880
Let's drink, bros.

655
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:01,680
Hi, everyone.

656
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:08,560
First of all, thank you all for coming.

657
00:43:09,760 --> 00:43:16,400
I do believe concerts are for music
and music connects people.

658
00:43:17,280 --> 00:43:20,000
Just like it did for me,
the day I met my boyfriend.

659
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:24,440
Tonight, I hope music
does the same for you.

660
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:27,399
Let's give it up for Something Sweet!

661
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:32,240
Whoo-hoo!

662
00:43:55,400 --> 00:43:57,959
♪ Do you still feel lonely? ♪

663
00:43:57,960 --> 00:44:01,400
♪ Open up, let in some company ♪

664
00:44:02,600 --> 00:44:05,399
♪ Count the stars up high ♪

665
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:08,520
♪ Being alone doesn't feel so right ♪

666
00:44:09,920 --> 00:44:13,039
♪ Look into my eyes, you'll see ♪

667
00:44:13,040 --> 00:44:16,240
♪ Can you feel we're meant to be? ♪

668
00:44:17,400 --> 00:44:20,720
♪ I counted thousands of stars ♪

669
00:44:20,920 --> 00:44:24,120
♪ Lighting up the night sky afar ♪

670
00:44:24,760 --> 00:44:28,000
♪ In my heart, you're my only love ♪

671
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:31,640
♪ Shining brighter than stars above ♪

672
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:37,199
♪ This true love belongs only to you ♪

673
00:44:37,200 --> 00:44:40,440
♪ No need to wait so long like others do ♪

674
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:44,559
♪ This true love for you means no harm ♪

675
00:44:44,560 --> 00:44:47,800
♪ Please accept it with open arms ♪

676
00:44:48,840 --> 00:44:52,079
♪ True love is nothing like flowers ♪

677
00:44:52,080 --> 00:44:55,800
♪ Blooming to prove their power ♪

678
00:44:56,200 --> 00:44:59,520
♪ True love waits for no sign ♪

679
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:04,280
♪ Open your heart, just give it a try ♪

680
00:45:06,185 --> 00:45:07,938
(Next Episode)
Hey, Arnold. What's up?

681
00:45:07,963 --> 00:45:08,816
Which is your house?

682
00:45:09,655 --> 00:45:12,422
Dean, can I switch places
with you? I want to talk to Jack.

683
00:45:12,453 --> 00:45:14,898
I'm not sure if I still want to act or not.

684
00:45:15,386 --> 00:45:19,506
I see, you're still not giving up on him.

685
00:45:19,531 --> 00:45:20,854
But you don't have to worry about me.

686
00:45:20,879 --> 00:45:22,148
Are you guys ready?

687
00:45:22,173 --> 00:45:22,970
What are you hoping for?

688
00:45:22,995 --> 00:45:24,116
I just want to have a date with you.

689
00:45:24,141 --> 00:45:27,462
My bro and bro-in-law have to be this
strong.

690
00:45:30,875 --> 00:45:34,149
Can I take a picture with you? I
'm going to make some content.
